Colombia Stocks: Chocolates Drops; Pacific Rubiales Rises

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-04-07T20:26:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/colombia-stocks-ecopetrol-falls-textiles-fabricato-increases.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.3 percent to 14,668.79, while the
Colcap Index increased 0.3 percent to 1,723.94.  Grupo Nacional de Chocolates SA (CHOCOLA)  ,  Colombia ’s
largest food producer by market value, dropped 1.3 percent to
23,100 pesos. Coffee prices that climbed to a 14-year high are
disrupting supplies of the beans, said Rodolfo Trampe Taubert,
 Mexico ’s candidate to head the  International Coffee
Organization .  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp (PREC)   climbed 1.5 percent
to 55,500 pesos. The Toronto-based  oil company  with fields in
Colombia said it plans to buy back as much as 11.6 million of
its common shares, according to a regulatory filing yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  